"'''The Kiss'''" is an oil-on-canvas painting with added gold leaf, silver, and platinum by the Austrian Symbolist painter [[Gustav Klimt]]. Painted between 1907 and 1908, it is the highpoint of his Golden Period and depicts a couple embracing, their bodies entwined in elaborately patterned robes.

The painting now hangs in the Österreichische Galerie Belvedere in [[Vienna]] and is considered a masterpiece of Vienna Jugendstil. It was acquired by the Belvedere shortly after its first exhibition, before Klimt had even finished it, and has rarely left Austria since.
